50|$|The {{work is a}} {{floating}} hull on a magnetic field, much as an anchorage for a ship. All dimensions have rigorous symbolic meaning. The <b>midship</b> <b>beam</b> of the hull corresponds to {{the diameter of the}} Earth, the ray of each end is proportional to that of the moon and the radius of the curvature of the frames is that of the sun. The competitors of the Trophy Jules Verne race around the Earth against time, with only the sun and the moon as companions and time keepers.|$|E

